<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911223-0155</DOCNO><DOCID>911223-0155.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Sony Pictures Entertainment</HL><DATE>12/23/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   SNE WNEWS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)HOME ELECTRONICS, FURNISHINGS, APPLIANCES (HMF)FILM, TELEVISION andamp; MUSIC INDUSTRIES (MOV)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY (REC)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)</NS><RE>FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   SONY PICTURES ENTERTAINMENT (Culver City, Calif.) -- Thisunit of Sony Corp. named Lawrence J. Ruisi executive vicepresident and a director, based in New York. Mr. Ruisi, 43years old, whose position is new, will be responsible for thecompany's world-wide exhibition operations, which includeabout 900 screens in 200 Loews theater locations. He alsowill work with other top executives on corporate strategicplanning, new business development and special projects. Mr.Ruisi had served from 1987 to 1990 as senior vice presidentand chief financial officer of Columbia PicturesEntertainment Inc., which Japan's Sony Corp. acquired in1989. He recently has been an executive consultant to SonyPictures. His appointment increases the unit's board to 15members. Sony Pictures also produces motion pictures,television programming, home video, operates studiofacilities and distributes filmed entertainment world-wide.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>